headline: Wall Street Landlords Loved These D.C. Suburbs. Rent Control Ended That.
summary: Multifamily buildings in Maryland’s Montgomery and Prince George’s counties, some of the most attractive in the U.S. to institutional investors, are now subject to strict rent control laws.
